5. Running the Project Locally:-

Step 1 - Clone the repository
git clone <your-repo-link>
cd collabspace

Step 2 - Setup backend
cd backend
npm install
Create a .env file:
PORT=5000
MONGO_URI=your_mongodb_connection_string
Start backend:
npm start

Step 3 - Setup frontend
cd frontend
npm install
npm start
Open:
http://localhost:3000

6. Features Implemented:-

-Real-time document syncing
-Room-based collaboration
-Auto-save functionality
-Live user presence list
-Branded header with logo
-Clean document-style layout

7. Possible Improvements:-

-Typing indicators
-Dark mode
-Version history
-Role-based access
-Deployment to production

8. Why I Built This

-This project was built to understand:
1.Real-time communication using WebSockets
2.Managing shared state across multiple users
3.Handling presence tracking
4.Integrating MongoDB persistence
5.Designing a clean, usable interface